                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.605,
                                "byte_start": 79980,
                                "byte_stop": 114462,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in Crist against Bretz will be announced by Mr. Justice Stewart."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.605,
                        "stop": 95.571,
                        "byte_start": 114462,
                        "byte_stop": 462308,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15043,
                            "name": "Potter Stewart",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/potter_stewart",
                            "last_name": "Stewart",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2687,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -353962800,
                                    "date_end": 362984400,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2687"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32752,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56350,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/potter_stewart.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8298,
                            "identifier": "potter_stewart"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.605,
                                "stop": 14.825,
                                "byte_start": 114462,
                                "byte_stop": 139330,
                                "text": "This case is here on appeal from the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.825,
                                "stop": 21.729,
                                "byte_start": 139330,
                                "byte_stop": 166916,
                                "text": "It involves another aspect of the constitutional guarantee against being twice put in jeopardy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.729,
                                "stop": 39.187,
                                "byte_start": 166916,
                                "byte_stop": 236819,
                                "text": "Precise issue is relatively simple one and it\u0027s a single one and it is whether the federal rule, governing the time when jeopardy attaches in a jury trial is binding on Montana through the Fourteenth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.187,
                                "stop": 46.225,
                                "byte_start": 236819,
                                "byte_stop": 264927,
                                "text": "The federal rule is that jeopardy attaches when the jury is impaneled and sworn."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.225,
                                "stop": 55.377,
                                "byte_start": 264927,
                                "byte_stop": 301498,
                                "text": "A Montana statue provides that jeopardy does not attach until the first witness is sworn."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.377,
                                "stop": 72.893,
                                "byte_start": 301498,
                                "byte_stop": 371611,
                                "text": "For the reasons stated in some detail in the written opinion of the Court filed today, we hold that the federal rule, that jeopardy attaches when the jury is impaneled and sworn is an integral part of the constitutional guarantee against double jeopardy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.893,
                                "stop": 78.333,
                                "byte_start": 371611,
                                "byte_stop": 393345,
                                "text": "And that accordingly it is binding upon the individual states."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.333,
                                "stop": 81.606,
                                "byte_start": 393345,
                                "byte_stop": 406406,
                                "text": "For these reasons the judgment before us is affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.606,
                                "stop": 84.957,
                                "byte_start": 406406,
                                "byte_stop": 419885,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Blackmun has filed a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.957,
                                "stop": 87.961,
                                "byte_start": 419885,
                                "byte_stop": 431902,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.961,
                                "stop": 95.571,
                                "byte_start": 431902,
                                "byte_stop": 462308,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell has also filed a dissenting opinion which the Chief Justice and Mr. Justice Rehnquist have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
